Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.52,0:00:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.20,0:00:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.95,0:00:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Georgios Kontaxis,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.74,0:00:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and together with Katie Skinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.59,0:00:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we are both very excited to be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.61,0:00:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,here, today, to tell you about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.28,0:00:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Privacy and your Apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.30,0:00:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We are members of Privacy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.73,0:00:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Engineering, Apple, and we work
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.69,0:00:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with teams across the company to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.57,0:00:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,deliver privacy into our
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.94,0:00:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,products.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.97,0:00:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, at Apple, we care about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.05,0:00:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And this quote from Tim Cook
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,reflects our philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.54,0:00:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We believe that privacy is a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.27,0:00:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,very basic foundation for a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.41,0:01:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,great app ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.82,0:01:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We think that great apps should
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.44,0:01:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,offer the best user experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.89,0:01:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,while respecting user privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.29,0:01:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, today, you will hear some
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.28,0:01:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,best practices to design your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.59,0:01:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,apps with privacy in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.13,0:01:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have existing apps, you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.90,0:01:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,will be very interested in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.45,0:01:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,updates to our platforms which
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.38,0:01:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,might affect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.41,0:01:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will learn about some
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.01,0:01:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting new privacy features
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.25,0:01:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that Apple is launching, this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.32,0:01:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.63,0:01:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that your apps may rely
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.29,0:01:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,on user data to deliver great
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.05,0:01:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,features.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.26,0:01:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it is important that you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.22,0:01:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,explain to your users how you're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.68,0:01:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,using their data, so they
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.45,0:01:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,understand what is going on and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.63,0:01:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they feel comfortable engaging
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.50,0:01:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.41,0:01:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, you need to get their
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.84,0:01:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,consent in the right context.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.29,0:01:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, as they're about to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.30,0:01:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,use a feature that relies on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.16,0:01:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,their data.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.10,0:01:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS has built-in mediation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.22,0:02:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanisms for transparency and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.81,0:02:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,consent, and you should consider
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.85,0:02:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,how you can best take advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.11,0:02:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.68,0:02:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS also offers users control
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.22,0:02:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,over their privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.55,0:02:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your apps need to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.23,0:02:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,cases based on the different
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.58,0:02:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy decisions the user might
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.43,0:02:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,make, including changing their
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.91,0:02:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,mind at a later time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.72,0:02:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's an example of how Maps is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.95,0:02:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,using the iOS built-in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.80,0:02:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanisms to prompt for the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.23,0:02:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,user's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.81,0:02:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, when prompting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.57,0:02:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Maps will clearly explain the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.52,0:02:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,use cases, navigation, nearby
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.52,0:02:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,search results, and estimated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.74,0:02:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,travel times.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.40,0:02:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the user chooses not to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.31,0:02:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,grant access to their location,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.15,0:02:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maps is able to handle that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.87,0:02:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,gracefully and provide a subset
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.04,0:02:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of its features.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.38,0:02:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If a user allows Maps the user
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.64,0:03:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,location, they will be aware
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.37,0:03:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,each time that happens, because
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.51,0:03:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there is an indicator in the iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.63,0:03:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,status bar to let them know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.08,0:03:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can always go to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.25,0:03:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Settings, Privacy, Location
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.41,0:03:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Services, see that Maps is using
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.98,0:03:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,their location and perhaps,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.32,0:03:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,revise their decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.24,0:03:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We also, know that your apps may
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.97,0:03:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,rely on identifiers, for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.77,0:03:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,example, to personalize the user
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.39,0:03:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,experience or to keep track of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.65,0:03:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.61,0:03:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, your users
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,might wonder whether their
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,actions in your app are tied to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.43,0:03:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,their device or to their person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.10,0:03:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, there are great ways to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.58,0:03:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,offer privacy friendly choices,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.31,0:03:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that users are comfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,engaging with your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.01,0:03:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Specifically, identifiers can be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.74,0:03:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,random, they can be anonymous,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.19,0:03:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they can be short-lived, and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.38,0:03:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they can be easy to reset.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.21,0:04:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And iOS offers built-in API for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.40,0:04:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you to be able to generate such
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.33,0:04:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.65,0:04:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you should adopt those
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.36,0:04:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of building your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.69,0:04:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example, consider the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.22,0:04:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Universally Unique Identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.03,0:04:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a random 128-bit value,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.62,0:04:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can generate using the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.35,0:04:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift code, shown here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you can see, three
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.83,0:04:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,consecutive calls using this API
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.55,0:04:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,will return three random
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.19,0:04:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,unrelated values.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.93,0:04:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And for example, you could
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.38,0:04:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,leverage the UIDs to generate
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.91,0:04:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,short-lived identifiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.91,0:04:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, you can associate a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,new UUID with each session in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.18,0:04:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.06,0:04:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Another example is the vendor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.61,0:04:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a more stable identifier,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.20,0:04:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is consistent across
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.46,0:04:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all apps associated with the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.73,0:04:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,same team.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.94,0:04:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, here, in the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.42,0:05:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,example table, two apps that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.52,0:05:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,belong to the same team all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.22,0:05:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,generate the same vendor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.32,0:05:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier, while a third app
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.73,0:05:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,belonging to a different team
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.26,0:05:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,will have its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.17,0:05:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, keep in mind that if all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.48,0:05:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,apps belonging to a particular
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.24,0:05:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,team are uninstalled from the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.19,0:05:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,user's device and later
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,reinstalled, they will get a new
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.47,0:05:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.00,0:05:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about collecting
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.99,0:05:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,data to enable your features.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.77,0:05:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Collecting data can be a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.67,0:05:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,benefit, but also, carries
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.50,0:05:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.18,0:05:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, users might be uncomfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.86,0:05:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,giving too much of their data,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.86,0:05:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do not sufficiently
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.95,0:05:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,justify the purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.00,0:05:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, consider the burden on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.15,0:05:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,your end to manage all that data
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.04,0:05:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep it safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.91,0:05:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you should consider
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:05:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,aggregating data, summarizing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it, and extracting only the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.43,0:05:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,information you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.69,0:06:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As an alternative, think whether
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.22,0:06:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a sample of the data would
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.92,0:06:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,suffice, or whether you can
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.17,0:06:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,process the data on device
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.53,0:06:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of sending their all
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,values to your server.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.41,0:06:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And later in this talk, you will
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.06,0:06:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,hear about some great new ways
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.03,0:06:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to process data on device, using
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.48,0:06:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS hardware and software.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.05,0:06:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Collecting raw data might reveal
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.39,0:06:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,additional information about the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.76,0:06:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.77,0:06:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And as mentioned, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,information that neither your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.53,0:06:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,users nor you might want to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.27,0:06:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,have.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.68,0:06:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example, consider you have
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a new feature in your app, and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to collect feedback
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.17,0:06:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to see how successful it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.36,0:06:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you could instrument your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.77,0:06:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,app to send back a timestamp to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.58,0:06:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,your server each time the users
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.64,0:06:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,engage with your feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.63,0:06:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And that would give you the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.73,0:06:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,information you're after.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.21,0:06:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you were to plot that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.05,0:06:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,data over a timeline, you could
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.15,0:07:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,also learn that user one is a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.32,0:07:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,morning person, because all of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.38,0:07:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,their timestamps are in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.78,0:07:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And user three opens your app at
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.70,0:07:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, another way to collect this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.66,0:07:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,information would be to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,''Well, I will have my app count
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.67,0:07:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the total number of times that a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.54,0:07:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,particular user engages with my
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,feature, and send that count
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.23,0:07:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,back to my server, once a day.''
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.03,0:07:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is a more privacy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.20,0:07:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,friendly way to learn the same
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.37,0:07:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,information about the feature,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.25,0:07:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's a customer or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.90,0:07:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you pay attention, you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.43,0:07:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,might realize that now you know
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.00,0:07:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that user one likes your feature
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.96,0:07:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the most, among your users.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.82,0:07:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not the question you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,were trying to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.24,0:07:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you were to rephrase the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.94,0:07:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,question as, ''How many users
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.67,0:07:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,engage with my feature more than
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,ten times a day?'' you could
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.74,0:07:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,have your app send back to your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.49,0:08:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,server, a Boolean flag, yes or
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,no, whether the user has
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.68,0:08:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,exceeded that threshold within
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.41,0:08:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.06,0:08:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And on your end, on the server,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.46,0:08:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you could calculate the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,percentage of users that have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,exceeded the threshold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In this particular case, 66%.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.71,0:08:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep that percentage on your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.40,0:08:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,server, keep track of it over
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.06,0:08:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,time as it changes, to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.60,0:08:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,understand how your feature
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.40,0:08:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,behaves, and discard any user
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.93,0:08:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,specific data.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now let's go over some
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.52,0:08:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,updates which might affect your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.93,0:08:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.19,0:08:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I mentioned, earlier, that when
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.52,0:08:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,apps ask for access to user data
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS will prompt users for their
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.25,0:08:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,consent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.66,0:08:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are cases where we
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.22,0:08:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,think that users need as much
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.95,0:08:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,information as possible to make
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.04,0:08:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,this decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.47,0:08:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And your app is responsible for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.06,0:08:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,providing this additional
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,context.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.65,0:08:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This additional context is in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.32,0:09:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the form of Purpose Strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.93,0:09:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And Purpose Strings are included
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.56,0:09:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the prompt shown to the user
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.36,0:09:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.12,0:09:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Purpose Strings are defined as
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.62,0:09:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,keys in the Info.plist file of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.05,0:09:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.02,0:09:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can define those keys in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.12,0:09:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode, like so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that those keys are
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.40,0:09:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,mandatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.77,0:09:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if your app is missing a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.53,0:09:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Purpose String and tries to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.19,0:09:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,access related data, it will
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,terminate with an error message
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.69,0:09:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,indicating which key is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.40,0:09:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 10, these are the cases
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.08,0:09:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,where Purpose Strings are
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.03,0:09:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,required.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.43,0:09:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And in iOS 11, we are making
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.96,0:09:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,changes to Location, Photos, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.20,0:09:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we're adding a Purpose String
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.50,0:09:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,for Core NFC.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Core location has enabled great
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.13,0:09:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,features in your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.88,0:09:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Users appreciate being able to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.71,0:10:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,navigate the world and find
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.71,0:10:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting places through their
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.52,0:10:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS device.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, we want users
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.30,0:10:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to always be in control of their
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.08,0:10:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.64,0:10:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in iOS 10 apps can ask for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.55,0:10:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,access to the user's location at
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.46,0:10:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,all times, or while the app is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.99,0:10:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in use.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.84,0:10:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11 users will be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.58,0:10:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,choose the When In Use option at
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.49,0:10:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.52,0:10:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.74,0:10:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What this means for you, is that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.28,0:10:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,your app will have to account
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.13,0:10:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for cases where the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.08,0:10:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,location is not available to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.12,0:10:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.72,0:10:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you need to define
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.98,0:10:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,additional Purpose Strings for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.56,0:10:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the When In Use option.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.70,0:10:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,As a reminder, when asking for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.31,0:11:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the user location make sure you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.23,0:11:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,do it in a meaningful way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.31,0:11:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you prompt after the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.11,0:11:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,user has engaged the feature
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.88,0:11:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that requires their location, so
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.80,0:11:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,they understand why they're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.93,0:11:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,being asked for their location.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,When you prompt, make sure your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.41,0:11:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Purpose String provides the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.55,0:11:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,necessary information for the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.41,0:11:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,user to make a good decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.41,0:11:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if possible, try asking for
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When In Use, and escalate to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.78,0:11:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Always after the user has some
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.13,0:11:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,time to experience your feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.13,0:11:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have an app on iOS 10
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.08,0:11:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that does not support the When
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.42,0:11:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In Use option, this is the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.55,0:11:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,prompt the user will see when
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.84,0:11:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,they upgrade to iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.37,0:11:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, they can choose
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.53,0:11:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the When In Use option, but
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.66,0:11:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a warning that the app
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.97,0:11:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,does not natively support it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.38,0:11:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have an app on iOS 10
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.87,0:12:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that does support both the When
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.00,0:12:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In Use and the Always option,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.49,0:12:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the prompt you will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.64,0:12:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Both Purpose Strings will be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.24,0:12:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,included in the prompt shown to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.89,0:12:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.20,0:12:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You should update your apps to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.96,0:12:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,feature a single Purpose String.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.75,0:12:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do that by defining
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.70,0:12:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a single key in your Info.plist
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.16,0:12:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,file, and use the Always and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.14,0:12:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When In Use key.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.18,0:12:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, let's talk about Photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.18,0:12:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The user's Photos library
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.66,0:12:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,contains a lot of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.59,0:12:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And we want you to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,leverage that information to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.51,0:12:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,deliver great features.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.46,0:12:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, we want to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.72,0:12:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,maintain a high level of user
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.31,0:12:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.39,0:12:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this year, we're adding two
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.82,0:12:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,new ways for your apps to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,interact with the Photos
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,library.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.07,0:12:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Specifically, users will be able
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.36,0:12:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to open a photo in your app
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.26,0:12:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,without the need for you to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.52,0:12:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,prompt for access to their
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.30,0:12:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,entire Photos library.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.51,0:13:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this will make them more
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.96,0:13:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,comfortable using your app,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.33,0:13:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because they will have better
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.89,0:13:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,control over their data.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.53,0:13:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're also, adding a Write only
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.61,0:13:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,access to the Photos library.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.29,0:13:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, if there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.92,0:13:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,game that wants to save a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.38,0:13:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,screenshot of the user
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,achievements, it can prompt for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.24,0:13:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Write, but not Read access to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.91,0:13:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the Photos library.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.50,0:13:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And users might be more willing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.46,0:13:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to grant that request.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.99,0:13:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of these changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.93,0:13:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when users upgrade their devices
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.41,0:13:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to iOS 11, existing apps will
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.92,0:13:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,re-prompt for access to the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.97,0:13:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Photos library.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.39,0:13:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want users to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.68,0:13:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,take advantage of this ability
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.01,0:13:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to open Photos in your app
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.52,0:13:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,without being prompted, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.48,0:13:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,adopt the Out Of Process Image
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.67,0:13:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Picker, and to find out more,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.21,0:13:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,please visit the Photos session.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great way to add a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.67,0:14:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,photo in a user's profile or use
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.00,0:14:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a photo in some other rare
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.02,0:14:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,action in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.78,0:14:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's look at the Write 0nly
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.79,0:14:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.85,0:14:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a prompt and a Purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.56,0:14:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,String, so if you want to adopt
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.57,0:14:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this, you need to decode the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.63,0:14:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Purpose String.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.89,0:14:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And make sure you provide enough
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.39,0:14:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,information for the users to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.94,0:14:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,decide whether they want to use
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.70,0:14:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.19,0:14:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about Core NFC.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.19,0:14:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,CoreNFC is a new and exciting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.44,0:14:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 framework, which allows
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.88,0:14:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,your app to use NFC reader modes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.14,0:14:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to interact with nearby NFC
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.64,0:14:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,tags.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.58,0:14:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, you can use NFC tags in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.58,0:14:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,your app in novel and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.37,0:14:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.84,0:14:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To adopt CoreNFC, you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.31,0:14:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,declare the corresponding
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.12,0:14:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Purpose String and provide the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.93,0:14:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,necessary context.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.72,0:14:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And this Purpose String will be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.78,0:15:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,included in the prompt shown to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.39,0:15:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the user every time your app
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.19,0:15:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,invokes CoreNFC.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.28,0:15:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about the watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.64,0:15:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We want your apps to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.88,0:15:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,do more with the watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this year, we're expanding
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.43,0:15:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the use of the microphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.64,0:15:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, in iOS 10, your app can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.47,0:15:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,ask for microphone access, and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.16,0:15:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,following the user's consent, it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.14,0:15:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,can start recording audio while
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.76,0:15:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in the foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.38,0:15:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In the new version of watchOS,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.58,0:15:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be able to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,recording while in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.87,0:15:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,background.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.05,0:15:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you stay in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.03,0:15:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,foreground you will be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.81,0:15:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,use the new API to record audio
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.41,0:15:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,without showing the built-in UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.89,0:15:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we want users to always
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.44,0:15:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,be aware that their microphone
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is active, if your app is in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.65,0:15:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,background, there will be an
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.36,0:15:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator on the watch face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.05,0:15:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the user taps on the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.83,0:16:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator your app will enter
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.78,0:16:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.87,0:16:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about Music.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We want your apps to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.58,0:16:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,take advantage of Music and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.40,0:16:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,create great features.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.03,0:16:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, part of this experience is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.46,0:16:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,having a frictionless way to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.82,0:16:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticate the user while
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.75,0:16:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,respecting their privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.44,0:16:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, if an app were
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.79,0:16:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask for the user's password
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.69,0:16:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to Music, that would be a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.49,0:16:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.76,0:16:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, apps should leverage
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.68,0:16:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that the users are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,already signed into Music on
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.33,0:16:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And iOS has a built-in mediation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.91,0:16:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanism for giving your apps
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.38,0:16:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,access to a Music token.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.39,0:16:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Following the user's consent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.45,0:16:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get that token and use
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.46,0:16:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it to access output APIs to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.66,0:17:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,retrieve personalized and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.64,0:17:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,non-personalized information.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.49,0:17:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, search the iTunes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.22,0:17:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,catalog or get information about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.94,0:17:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the user's library.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.34,0:17:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And remember, because the user
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.54,0:17:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,will have control over which
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.04,0:17:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,apps get this token, make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.33,0:17:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you provide the necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.49,0:17:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,context in the Purpose String
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.27,0:17:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for users to understand what you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.36,0:17:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,want to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.98,0:17:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.62,0:17:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.95,0:17:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,great way for users to browse
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.68,0:17:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the web in your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.12,0:17:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And in iOS 10 Safari cookies and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.47,0:17:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,website data were available in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.05,0:17:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,SVC instances, in Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.98,0:17:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller instances, in your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.84,0:17:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.29,0:17:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This will change.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.39,0:17:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in iOS 11 users will be
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.00,0:17:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,able to use an account to log in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.57,0:17:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a website in your app and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.76,0:18:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps, use a different account
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.35,0:18:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if they want to, to log into the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.16,0:18:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,same website in Safari, or some
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.07,0:18:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,other app.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.94,0:18:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we think that gives users
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.46,0:18:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,more control.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.97,0:18:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Specifically, what this means is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.49,0:18:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that Safari and Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.81,0:18:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller instances will have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.85,0:18:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,separate data stores for cookies
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.72,0:18:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and other website's data.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.82,0:18:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And what this means for you and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.19,0:18:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,your users, is that they will
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.88,0:18:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,still be able to browse the web
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.99,0:18:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in your app the same way as
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.50,0:18:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But they may have to login,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.60,0:18:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,again, to some of the sites they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.25,0:18:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.60,0:18:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what it looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.02,0:18:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, I have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.35,0:18:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple.com cookies in Safari, and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.57,0:18:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I have different cookies in your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.28,0:18:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.44,0:18:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this concludes the updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.59,0:18:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.25,0:18:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,invite Katie onstage to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.24,0:18:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,all about some exciting new
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.72,0:18:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy features that Apple is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.55,0:18:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,launching, this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.94,0:18:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Katie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.52,0:19:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.13,0:19:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Georgios.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm going to focus on some
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.66,0:19:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,new privacy features, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.76,0:19:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,provide an update on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.91,0:19:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,differential privacy, that we
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.74,0:19:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.84,0:19:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to start with on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.03,0:19:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,device processing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, On-Device processing has a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.52,0:19:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.06,0:19:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the first ones, is it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.46,0:19:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,enables your functionality to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.69,0:19:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,run anywhere your users are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether they're at the beach,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.21,0:19:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,like this, or on an airplane
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.32,0:19:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,flight, or even in areas of poor
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.71,0:19:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,cellular connectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.50,0:19:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It also, avoids network latency,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.64,0:19:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as depending on where your users
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are, this may take longer than
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.19,0:19:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the actual processing that you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.79,0:19:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,want to accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.38,0:19:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The speed of our devices, your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.31,0:19:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhones, our iPads, it keeps
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.51,0:19:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,increasing and increasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.53,0:19:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The iPhone 7 is 120 times the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.92,0:19:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,processing power of the original
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.92,0:19:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.75,0:20:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, think through the different
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.00,0:20:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,tasks that you once thought were
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.57,0:20:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,not feasible on device, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.99,0:20:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,should reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.42,0:20:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you all are at the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.14,0:20:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy session, I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.78,0:20:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,talk a little bit more about the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.97,0:20:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy related benefits of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.95,0:20:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,On-Device processing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.12,0:20:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the first ones is access
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.65,0:20:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to user data.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.85,0:20:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there are many different
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.55,0:20:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,types of sensitive data on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.90,0:20:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,device.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.02,0:20:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you're clear to your
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.23,0:20:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,users about how you plan to use
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.56,0:20:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that data.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.64,0:20:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Like for instance, if you tell
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.95,0:20:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,your users that the photo that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.00,0:20:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you take, if you apply a nice
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.60,0:20:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,halo on it, maybe a filter, that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.03,0:20:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,stays on their device.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.58,0:20:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Until they choose to share it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.86,0:20:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with another user, or maybe back
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.89,0:20:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.62,0:20:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, users are going to be more
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.05,0:20:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,likely to want to grant you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.40,0:20:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,access to their data, and feel
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.09,0:20:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,more comfortable about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.98,0:20:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,On-Device, you can also take
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.54,0:20:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,advantage of all the different
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,security features that are built
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.43,0:21:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,into our platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.76,0:21:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These are things like data
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.57,0:21:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,protection, the Keychain, that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.20,0:21:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,allow you to more securely take
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,care of user's data, without you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.93,0:21:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,having to implement it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.13,0:21:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.46,0:21:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in past developer sessions,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.20,0:21:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,they're a great resource for you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.73,0:21:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to go and learn more about these
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.03,0:21:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,security features.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.59,0:21:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I would encourage you to go
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.11,0:21:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,check out ''Protecting Secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.08,0:21:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,With the Keychain''.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.87,0:21:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great place to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.87,0:21:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when you're using and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.04,0:21:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping the data on device, that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.98,0:21:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,means you don't have to write
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.68,0:21:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,code to send that data to your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.79,0:21:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,server.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.41,0:21:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to write code to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.31,0:21:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,securely manage and make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.92,0:21:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that, that data on your server
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.73,0:21:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.29,0:21:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you all know the less code
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.79,0:21:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to write, that means
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.20,0:21:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the less bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.37,0:21:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the less bugs are less bugs
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.12,0:21:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that an attacker can take
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.34,0:22:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,advantage of.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.83,0:22:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a data breach is very
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.85,0:22:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,serious, and there are a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.06,0:22:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.50,0:22:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But one of the consequences is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.36,0:22:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of user trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.92,0:22:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, technologies like this can
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.60,0:22:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,help you avoid that, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.57,0:22:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.02,0:22:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,four new frameworks that allow
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.74,0:22:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you to do these common tasks on
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.38,0:22:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,device.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.55,0:22:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, any type of processing that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.44,0:22:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you do within your app, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.93,0:22:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,move to on device.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.52,0:22:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But here are four frameworks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.72,0:22:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that make it easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.32,0:22:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is CoreML, Core
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.54,0:22:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Machine Learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.14,0:22:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this allows you to have a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.38,0:22:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,simple interface to load and run
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.37,0:22:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,pretrained models.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.10,0:22:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There a lot of different models
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.30,0:22:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that it supports.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.81,0:22:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But one of them is neural
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.00,0:22:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,networks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.70,0:22:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The second framework I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.84,0:22:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about is VisionKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.35,0:22:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, VisionKit allows you to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.76,0:22:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,identify faces within a photo,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.10,0:22:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as do scene
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.27,0:23:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,classification, and group photos
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.96,0:23:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by the contents of the scene and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.82,0:23:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.55,0:23:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the ones that I'm most
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.32,0:23:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,excited about is ARKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.20,0:23:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think augmented reality is a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.25,0:23:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,place where there's lots of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.33,0:23:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting things to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.50,0:23:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't wait to get it in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.13,0:23:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all of your hands, to see what
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.92,0:23:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of experiences you guys
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.72,0:23:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,create for our users.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.90,0:23:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, ARKit can allow you to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.28,0:23:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,locate the device, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.67,0:23:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,items in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.56,0:23:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, it allows you to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.98,0:23:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,augment on top of a camera
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.03,0:23:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.85,0:23:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, lastly, we have NLP,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.38,0:23:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Natural Language Processing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.29,0:23:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This allows you to identify what
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.86,0:23:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,language a customer may have be
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.32,0:23:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,entering text with, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.07,0:23:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also allows you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.49,0:23:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,tokenization, as well as named
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.59,0:23:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,entity recognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.87,0:23:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd encourage you to go
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.67,0:23:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,check out the talk introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.62,0:23:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,CoreML, later this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.33,0:23:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This will provide an overview of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.42,0:24:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the different features available
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.13,0:24:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can take advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.56,0:24:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,on device.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.73,0:24:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, I'm going to talk about a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.98,0:24:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,new framework available in iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.58,0:24:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.00,0:24:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called Device Check.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.02,0:24:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there are many developers
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.12,0:24:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who are currently using a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.55,0:24:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,variety of techniques to try to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.67,0:24:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,identify devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.00,0:24:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they may be trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.39,0:24:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,identify and answer questions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.23,0:24:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,like, ''Has this device received
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.68,0:24:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a free trial?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.24,0:24:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Has this device participated in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.47,0:24:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,fraudulent activity?'' Or, ''Has
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.16,0:24:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this device done something that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.42,0:24:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is against your app's developer
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.72,0:24:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines?'' Now, in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.41,0:24:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve that goal, many
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.93,0:24:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,developers, though, I'm sure
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.39,0:24:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,none of you in this room, may be
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.96,0:24:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,collecting lots of information
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.82,0:24:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to associate some state
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.65,0:24:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with that device.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.98,0:24:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to do that, they may be
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.26,0:24:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,collecting lots of information
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.70,0:25:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,like, how's the device set up?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.86,0:25:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What information is stored on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.92,0:25:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.99,0:25:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And these developers may not
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.50,0:25:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,want to have this level of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.76,0:25:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.70,0:25:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All they want to do is associate
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.27,0:25:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,some state with that device, in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.93,0:25:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.63,0:25:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, DeviceCheck allows you to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.81,0:25:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,associate state with the device.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.27,0:25:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is done in a privacy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.93,0:25:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,friendly way that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.77,0:25:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve without collecting
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.29,0:25:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,unnecessary information.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.33,0:25:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, DeviceCheck allows you to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.68,0:25:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,store two bits of information,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.81,0:25:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as a timestamp
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.44,0:25:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,associated with one device.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.00,0:25:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is per team ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.29,0:25:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can store 00, 01, 10, or
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.40,0:25:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,11.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.66,0:25:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's up to you to think
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.08,0:25:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,about what this means to your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.06,0:25:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,application and your app logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.05,0:25:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this information will be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.86,0:26:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,maintained by Apple through
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.25,0:26:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,until you reset it, or you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.65,0:26:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,update the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.24,0:26:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this means it will be stored
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.77,0:26:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by Apple through deletion of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.41,0:26:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,your app, reinstallation of your
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.51,0:26:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,app, through erase all contents
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.85,0:26:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and settings, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.69,0:26:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,transfer of that device between
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.54,0:26:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.60,0:26:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we know users sell devices
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.44,0:26:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.26,0:26:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We know they transfer them to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.95,0:26:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,other siblings or other people
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.50,0:26:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.37,0:26:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this information will be
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.76,0:26:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,maintained through that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.47,0:26:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as I mentioned before, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.05,0:26:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,up to you to figure out what
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.06,0:26:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,these states mean to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.25,0:26:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, an example would be for app
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.69,0:26:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A, if a user has completed a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.53,0:26:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,free trial they will be assigned
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.25,0:26:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,state 01.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.19,0:26:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you could have a different
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.82,0:26:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,app, app B.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.43,0:26:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that same information, that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.60,0:26:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,same state that a free trial has
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.26,0:26:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,been assigned or completed could
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.35,0:26:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,be assigned 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.56,0:26:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you to make that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.65,0:26:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.13,0:27:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I want to go through the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.79,0:27:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,flow and make sure you guys
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.95,0:27:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,understand how this works in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.47,0:27:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.03,0:27:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's say there's an app
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.36,0:27:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a news app.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.49,0:27:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And like I said before, it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.03,0:27:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,grants a seven day free trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.51,0:27:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when my free trial is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.90,0:27:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,completed the app wants to set
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.30,0:27:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,my state to 01.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.52,0:27:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, first thing it's going to do
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.76,0:27:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is query for a device check
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.39,0:27:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,token on device, send it to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.78,0:27:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,their app server, and then via
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.33,0:27:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,server communication set the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.05,0:27:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,state and send it to Apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.03,0:27:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, send over the token and the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.56,0:27:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,state that wants to be set.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.92,0:27:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then I decide that maybe I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.97,0:27:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,not a huge fan of that news app,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.51,0:27:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.43,0:27:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to delete it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.39,0:27:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, I miss it couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.24,0:27:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,weeks later, so I decide I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.06,0:27:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,going to reinstall the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.05,0:27:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,On launch, that app wants to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.03,0:27:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,decide, ''should that user or
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.59,0:27:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that device be given another
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.94,0:27:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,free trial''?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.69,0:28:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, query for the token, send it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.22,0:28:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to the app server the same way,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.68,0:28:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and this time query for the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.23,0:28:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,state of the device.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.33,0:28:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then because that device was
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.45,0:28:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,last set as 01, it will be sent
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.86,0:28:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the app server.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.91,0:28:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point it's the app's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.95,0:28:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,job to figure out what to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.11,0:28:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,next.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.33,0:28:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Should that device be granted
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.99,0:28:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,another free trial?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.76,0:28:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Should that device be granted,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.83,0:28:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe, a shorter trial?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.67,0:28:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Or no trial at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.02,0:28:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you to make that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.32,0:28:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.65,0:28:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as I said before, devices
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.13,0:28:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,can transfer between users.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.32,0:28:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's say I sell my device
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.78,0:28:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to Georgios, because I want a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.87,0:28:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,different phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.86,0:28:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a new gold one, this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.28,0:28:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.50,0:28:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then Georgios wants to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.13,0:28:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,install the same app.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.04,0:28:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He likes the same news app.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.80,0:28:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's going to query for the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.09,0:28:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,token the same way, send it to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.04,0:28:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,its app server, and then, query
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.32,0:28:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.08,0:28:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, 01 will be returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.42,0:29:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And this case, Georgios has not
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.93,0:29:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,gotten a free trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.18,0:29:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you need to think about how
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.37,0:29:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle these type of cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.01,0:29:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, make sure that you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.49,0:29:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,way that customers can reach out
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.56,0:29:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or escalate if they are
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.68,0:29:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing issues with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.24,0:29:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And they need to come and reach
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.03,0:29:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,out to you, because at Apple, we
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.41,0:29:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have any idea what these
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.58,0:29:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,states correspond to.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.96,0:29:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, I'm going to quickly go
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.35,0:29:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,through what a sample query
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.47,0:29:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could look like.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.09,0:29:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, here's the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.03,0:29:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,device token, the transaction
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.24,0:29:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,ID, which you generate, as well
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.34,0:29:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as a timestamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.09,0:29:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, here's the response from
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.74,0:29:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple with the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.61,0:29:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, if you want to update
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.42,0:29:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the state, again have the device
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.36,0:29:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,token, your transaction ID that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.73,0:29:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you generate, as well as the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.29,0:29:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,timestamp and the state you want
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.43,0:29:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to set.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.99,0:29:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're using DeviceCheck
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.63,0:29:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure to think through these
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.10,0:29:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,best practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.14,0:29:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you handle the case
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.86,0:30:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,where devices are transferred
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.41,0:30:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,between users.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.83,0:30:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A device's behavior can change
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.70,0:30:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.85,0:30:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, think about the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.05,0:30:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,recency of the data.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.17,0:30:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If the state was set a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.52,0:30:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ago, maybe that means something
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.52,0:30:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,different to you than if it was
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.20,0:30:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.03,0:30:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This should be part of your
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.72,0:30:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,app's logic, but not the sole
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.62,0:30:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,source.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.83,0:30:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And think through how you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.86,0:30:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,represent this state in the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.44,0:30:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When Georgios goes to launch the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.80,0:30:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,app for the first time, you want
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.30,0:30:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a fresh experience for
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.69,0:30:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.80,0:30:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, make sure you think through
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.44,0:30:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.31,0:30:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you should be using
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.66,0:30:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,platform supported identifiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.75,0:30:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the application
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.88,0:30:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier, the vendor
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.58,0:30:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,identifier, as well as the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.12,0:30:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,advertising identifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.68,0:30:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We will continue to remove and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.30,0:30:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to remove entropy on our
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.30,0:30:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,out-of-the-app sandbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.91,0:30:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we have before, we will
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.03,0:30:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to identify areas of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.57,0:30:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,entropy and put them either
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.56,0:30:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,behind user control or remove
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.15,0:30:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.95,0:31:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, I'm going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.46,0:31:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligent Tracking Protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.01,0:31:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, we're working to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.10,0:31:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,reduce cross-web tracking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.97,0:31:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, since the beginning, WebKit
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.16,0:31:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and Safari have been leaders in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.63,0:31:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,user privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.75,0:31:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One example of this is blocking
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.25,0:31:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,third party cookies by default.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.33,0:31:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I want to get this out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.76,0:31:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there, that Intelligent Tracking
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.24,0:31:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Protection is not about blocking
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.80,0:31:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.51,0:31:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what this technology
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.43,0:31:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.38,0:31:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It dynamically detects online
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.02,0:31:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,tracking across the sites that a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.92,0:31:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,user visits.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.35,0:31:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And using an on-device
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.88,0:31:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,classifier, it will identify
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.76,0:31:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,tracking domains.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.39,0:31:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Once a tracking domain is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.61,0:31:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,identified, then it will isolate
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.35,0:31:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the third party cookies, as well
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.25,0:31:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as website data for that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.66,0:31:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,website.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.97,0:31:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, periodically, that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.17,0:31:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,data will be purged.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.67,0:31:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if the user interacts with
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.31,0:31:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that domain, that is taken as a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.35,0:31:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,signal that the user is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.73,0:32:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in that website.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.99,0:32:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, that website will be
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.02,0:32:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,whitelisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.66,0:32:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's go through an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.86,0:32:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if example.com is identified
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.12,0:32:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as a tracker, and the user
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.75,0:32:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,visits site 1, that embeds
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.67,0:32:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,example.com, example.com will
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.05,0:32:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,set the cookie foo.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.04,0:32:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a user goes to site 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.61,0:32:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which also embeds example.com,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.85,0:32:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but here, example.com does not
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.07,0:32:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,have access to the cookie foo.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.18,0:32:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then it will set cookie bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.58,0:32:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, over time these
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.60,0:32:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,cookies will be purged.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.37,0:32:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, no cookies will be deleted
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.99,0:32:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from first party websites.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.37,0:32:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, if the user
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.50,0:32:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,interacts with your website via
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.02,0:32:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,click, a tap, entering a form,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.66,0:32:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then note it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.69,0:32:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,whitelisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.65,0:32:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You should not rely on storage
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.70,0:32:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,if the user does not interact
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.39,0:32:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with your website.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.31,0:32:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is an important one to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.46,0:33:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,understand; if your analytics
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.98,0:33:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,package relies on third party
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.86,0:33:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,cookies, they may be affected.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.81,0:33:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we're trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.92,0:33:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve, here, is that users
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.80,0:33:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,only have long-term persistent
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.06,0:33:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,tracking and cookies from sites
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.40,0:33:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that they actually intersect
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.06,0:33:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.55,0:33:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They actually interact with.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.13,0:33:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, all the other tracking
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.10,0:33:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as the user navigates and visits
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.83,0:33:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,websites will be proactively
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.67,0:33:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.58,0:33:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lastly, we have an update on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.85,0:33:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Differential Privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.65,0:33:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Differential Privacy was
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.03,0:33:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,launched on iOS and macOS, last
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.00,0:33:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,year.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.86,0:33:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, we've collected
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.18,0:33:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of privately donated
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.46,0:33:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,data per day, and it allowed us
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.58,0:33:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to build user features with
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.37,0:33:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.89,0:33:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I want to talk about two
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.58,0:33:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,new use cases, this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.61,0:33:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is collecting what
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.96,0:34:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,data is commonly stored in
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.86,0:34:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,HealthKit.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.10,0:34:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one of the challenges of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.68,0:34:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,working on sensitive features,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.82,0:34:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or features that have sensitive
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.38,0:34:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,data, is you want to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.63,0:34:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,how those features are being
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.94,0:34:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,used.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.27,0:34:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to understand what's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.54,0:34:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,resonating, where users are
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.14,0:34:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,falling into issues or errors
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.87,0:34:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,are occurring.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.94,0:34:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know that collecting
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.47,0:34:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,data about what they're actually
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.96,0:34:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,interacting with may have more
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.63,0:34:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,information than you really
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.68,0:34:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,need.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.84,0:34:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one example here is, if you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.08,0:34:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,collect what type of data, what
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.30,0:34:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,data types the user has stored
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.67,0:34:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,on their device, things like
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.72,0:34:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,blood glucose.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.90,0:34:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Things like Workout, that could
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.79,0:34:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,convey other additional
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.14,0:34:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,information about their health
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.67,0:34:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or about any conditions they
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.91,0:34:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,have, or how active they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.37,0:34:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And we don't really need that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.06,0:34:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,level of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.47,0:34:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's why it's so exciting
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.06,0:34:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to have Differential Privacy at
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.39,0:34:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple, because we can still get
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.74,0:34:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,information to continue to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.25,0:34:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,iterate and build our features,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.53,0:34:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,while respecting user privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.83,0:35:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, last year in the Privacy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.81,0:35:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,session at the Developer
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.06,0:35:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Conference, Julian [assumed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.35,0:35:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,spelling] did a great job
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.19,0:35:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,deep-diving into how
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.48,0:35:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Differential Privacy works at
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.96,0:35:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.76,0:35:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, we collect privatized
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.41,0:35:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,donations like emoji, and as
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.43,0:35:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more users contribute
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.12,0:35:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,these privatized emojis, we
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.90,0:35:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,learn what are the most popular
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.01,0:35:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,emojis.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.66,0:35:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But the key part here, is we
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.77,0:35:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,learned nothing that's
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.06,0:35:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,associated by an individual
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.54,0:35:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,user.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.97,0:35:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information about how
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.42,0:35:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Differential Privacy works at
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.73,0:35:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple, I would encourage you all
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.15,0:35:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at our session from last
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.35,0:35:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,year's Developer's Conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.07,0:35:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this year we're applying the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.26,0:35:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,same process to health data
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.10,0:35:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,types.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.10,0:35:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we will learn the most
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.42,0:35:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,popular health data types, but
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.38,0:35:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,with learning nothing about the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.61,0:35:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,individual user.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.30,0:35:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The second case is trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.03,0:35:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,learn websites that either are
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.83,0:36:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,very slow or take up a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.36,0:36:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,battery life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.97,0:36:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We all want a fast, speedy web.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.59,0:36:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't necessarily want to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.65,0:36:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,learn everything that a user is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.46,0:36:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,visiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.41,0:36:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lot of information
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.93,0:36:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,about that user, depending on
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.70,0:36:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,their web searches.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.28,0:36:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is another example
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.48,0:36:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,where we get to use Differential
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.79,0:36:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Privacy to then, reach out to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.80,0:36:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,these developers who maybe, have
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.75,0:36:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,issues or are writing slow
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.09,0:36:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,sites.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.84,0:36:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then we can improve the web
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.10,0:36:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.96,0:36:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in summary, we are all here
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.67,0:36:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,today, and listening online and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.26,0:36:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,here this week in an effort to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.73,0:36:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,build great features for our
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.06,0:36:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.60,0:36:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Make something that our users
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.74,0:36:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,will love.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.79,0:36:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Make something that our users
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.90,0:36:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,think is fun, or maybe makes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.85,0:36:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,their lives easier, their jobs
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.64,0:36:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.99,0:36:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I want you to take away
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.83,0:36:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,from the past 40 minutes, is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.67,0:36:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,several techniques and concepts
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.76,0:36:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can apply within your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.06,0:36:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,own app.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.65,0:36:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is consent and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.53,0:37:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,transparency.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.16,0:37:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to think about what
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.82,0:37:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you're saying in your Purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.26,0:37:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Strings and be clear to your
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.46,0:37:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.61,0:37:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, adopt While In Use
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.82,0:37:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,location.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.70,0:37:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Together, we can build a healthy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.69,0:37:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,app ecosystem, and DeviceCheck
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.68,0:37:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.94,0:37:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to build a healthy web
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.79,0:37:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,for everyone, and Intelligent
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.69,0:37:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Tracking Protection is a key
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.21,0:37:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,part of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.52,0:37:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,With Differential Privacy, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.33,0:37:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,building features and learning
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.02,0:37:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,how to build better features,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.33,0:37:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,while protecting user privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.05,0:37:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one of the great things
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.36,0:37:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,about my job at Apple is I get
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.83,0:37:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to work with a bunch of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.86,0:37:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,different teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.21,0:37:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And everyone's working so hard
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.92,0:37:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to build fantastic features and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.98,0:37:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,APIs for you guys to take
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.33,0:37:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,advantage of, that will make our
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.38,0:37:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,users be delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.93,0:37:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that same passion, I get to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.71,0:37:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,apply and work with great people
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.15,0:37:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to apply to building privacy in,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.96,0:37:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.19,0:37:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And making sure that we all are
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.76,0:38:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,building great features and
